# Example VarMap Mapping File
# This file demonstrates the mapping format used by VarMap for renaming variables.
# Each line represents an identifier in the JavaScript code with the following fields:
# - LINE:COL: Position in the source file
# - TYPE: Type of identifier (ref, var, param, etc.)
# - SCOPE: Scope where the identifier is defined
# - ORIGINAL: Original name in the source code
# - CANONICAL: Canonicalized name assigned by VarMap
# - NEW_NAME: User-provided replacement name (for --map mode)
# - CONTEXT: Code snippet showing the identifier in context
#
# LINE:COL TYPE SCOPE ORIGINAL CANONICAL NEW_NAME CONTEXT
1:10 ref global a fn_1 addNumbers "function a(b,c){var d=b+c;return d;}"
1:12 ref fn_a b param_1 firstNumber "function a(b,c){var d=b+c;return d;}"
1:14 ref fn_a c param_2 secondNumber "function a(b,c){var d=b+c;return d;}"
1:21 ref fn_a d var_1 sum "function a(b,c){var d=b+c;return d;}"